wikipedia_page.main: Geraldine Emma May Jebb CBE (1886 - 28 December 1959), known as Gem Jebb, was the daughter of Heneage Horsley Jebb and Geraldine Croker Russell. She was the Principal of Bedford College, University of London, from 1930–1951, the first higher education women's college in the United Kingdom. She was unmarried.
